9140c0e5-216a-4e54-923d-cc72438a82b6.110f059f-8c32-4bd6-81d0-83d6b3989673.description=
Computes a mathematical operation.

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the first value
value2 - the second value
operator - operation to perform (+,-,*,/,%);

Responses\:
success - the expression was evaluated.
failure - the expression could not be evaluated.

Returns\: the value of the expression.
9140c0e5-216a-4e54-923d-cc72438a82b6.156f9cb1-611f-4b17-b340-04eea29554c8.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Pings the requested machine from a remote host

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or IP address of the host to ping from.
username - The username to use to authenticate to host.
password - The password to use to authenticate to host.
target - The target server to ping.
packets - The number of packets to send to target.
packetSize - The size of packets to send to target.

Responses\:
passed - a successful connection was made
failure - target did not respond to ping.
Connection Error - Unable to connect to host.
Unknown Target - could not resolve target to a valid IP address

Extra Results\:
output - raw output of the results
address - actual IP address pinged
% Packet Loss - The percentage of packets that ping replies were received for.
average latency - The average ping response time in milliseconds.
max latency - The maximum response time of all the pings (in milliseconds).
min latency - the minimum number of milliseconds it took to receive a ping response.
9140c0e5-216a-4e54-923d-cc72438a82b6.d6e83259-238e-4689-b232-00568b8addf4.transition.description=Unable to compute difference between ping times. 9140c0e5-216a-4e54-923d-cc72438a82b6.da2abcfe-14a7-4436-a476-fb3fdcc36577.description= Checks if a threshold matches a measuredValue and creates a diagnostic summary if they do not. inputs\: measuredValue - value measured. threshold - A threshold to compare the measuredValue against.. Threshold function - (\=\=, \!\=, >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold diagnostic name - the name of this diagnostic. diagnostic so far - The output of previous diagnostics, used for chaining diagnostics together. recommended resolution - A reccomendation for resolving the problem if the measured value is outside the threshold. responses\: success - sublist is contained in container. 9140c0e5-216a-4e54-923d-cc72438a82b6.description=
This flow uses a trace route to attempt to localize a network failure.

Note\: if a route cannot be found, it will take a long time to enumerate each hop. If this happens at the beginning of the trace route, the trace route may time out with a 500 server error. In this case, decrease the maxhops count.

inputs\:
host - The host to traceroute from.
username - credentials for host.
password - credentials for host.
target - The host to traceroute to.
hopTimeThreshold - The maximum amount of acceptable time between hops.
maxhops - The maximum number of hops to traceroute over.
diagnostic so far - The diagnostic so far, used for chaining diagnostics.
notifyMethod - How the user should be informed of the diagnostic's output.

Responses\:
success - The operation was successful.
failure - something went wrong.

Returns\:
A human readable diagnostic (updated diagnostic so far)
